SIMPLE: engaged
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Engaged
<hw>En*gaged"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Occupied; employed; busy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pledged; promised; especially, having the affections
pledged; promised in marriage; affianced; betrothed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Greatly interested; of awakened zeal;
earnest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Involved; esp., involved in a hostile encounter;
<as>as, the <ex>engaged</ex> ships continued the fight</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Engaged column</b></col>. <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <cd>Same as
<cref>Attached column</cref>. See under <er>Attach</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos></cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Engagedly</ent>⟦br⟧
